Bluzer's Guitar Hero Series For Phase Shift *04/14/13*

by bluzer » Wed Sep 12, 2012 2:07 am



.......

Q1: What's Phase Shift?
A1: If you don't know, then you shouldn't be in this thread...If you want to know. GO HERE => Phase Shift

Q2: Can I play these with FoF/FoFiX?
A2: Unfortunately NO. These new charts have gameplay mechanics that will not work properly in those games.

Q3: Jdownloader DLC container is only showing one file name, and I get an error.
A3: Right click the main folder > Check online status, it should populate with the proper file names. If its still not working try the Beta 2 version > http://board.jdownloader.org/showthread.php?t=37365

Q4: When will you post more songs?
A4: Right now, as of first posting this. I'll updated the thread with a new MSL for each game/each week. So other people who are helping can catch up.

Q5: What about the RB Series for Phase Shift or RB3 Thread(MF disabled the account and all links in it), when are they going to be updated?
A5: As soon as we get the MSL's done for this GH series thread, We'll get back to doing RB Series DLC songs. As for RB3, that's still on the waiting list, no ETA on that.

*NEW*
Q6: I am getting "fatal error" in my status of a link
A6: Could be one of two things, 1) you didn't do what it says in Q3... 2) you ticked the "dont bother me again" check box when it came answering the CAPTCHA question(both are not confirmed, so if it works for you, please say so).

.......

Well here we are! After so bloody long, we can finally get this out there.

It has been a long-long time coming for PC users to have properly ripped GH charts! Sadly, these chart will not work in FoF/FoFiX/GH3 PC without some editing.

All previous GH charts/audio were ripped with/from the RawkSD/Wii files. With the charts being ripped by RawkSD, they were intended for RB importing & to a lesser extent FoFiX.
These charts ripped with RawkSD were stripped from all amenities that made GH charts different. Not only that, aside from Open Bass notation, the rest of the features are not supported by FoFiX.

These new rips contain fully separated audio(in similar fashion to the RB Series thread), they are ripped from the x360 audio(not WoR unfortunately).
Past FoFiX rips contained Wii audio and believe me, it did not sound that great.

Whats new in these rips?
  • Ripped X360 audio, default sample rate @ 48000hz
  • Complete Separated Audio, all tracks.
  • Audio tweaks where needed(some songs are quite/on par with RB audio)
  • Guitar Hero specific gameplay mechanics
    • Extended Sustains
    • 5-Lane drums
    • Expert+ drums
    • ALL vocals/lyrics ripped & working(currently in PS, lyrics are displayed only, eventually PART VOCALS will be supported[hopefully])
    • Slider Notes(supported, but the real life guitar instrument that has the slider pad is not, so it makes them tap notes[driver problems])
    • Open Bass Notes
    • added solo sections
    • *secret chart found in GHM, only playable with these charts*

Raynebc, Without his work, none of this would have been possible. He after all learned the (GH QB/NOTE format) & made it possible to import into EOF(and he put up with my constant PMs regarding bug fixes! )
JD2504, Did GHSH/GHWoR(fixed a couple songs in GHM too!), and also made our life easier with his SIT tool(Song Information Tool[song.ini generator] it truly is a time saver) & that sweet ass logo. =D

OddBrother, Did BH *Includes Pro-D*, helping with GH5DLC.
